description:
mid-range 6-core processor based on the all-new AMD Zen 4 microarchitecture (codenamed Raphael). The chip is made using an advanced 5nm process technology, sharpened to work with DDR5 RAM with AMD EXPO auto-overclocking technology and is designed for installation in motherboards with the AMD AM5 socket, introduced in 2022. The Ryzen 5 7600X BOX chip is based on 6 progressive Zen 4 cores with a base clock speed of 4.7 GHz, which can be automatically overclocked to 5.3 GHz using Turbo Core technology.

The cores support multi-threading technology, which allows each core to simultaneously execute two computational threads, thereby increasing the overall performance of the processor. Thanks to the new architecture, AMD engineers were able to double the size of the third level cache, bringing its total to 32 MB. With faster clock speeds, larger caches, and an optimized architecture, the Ryzen 5 Raphael 7600X BOX delivers nearly 30% faster single-core performance than comparable Zen 3 CPUs. creative authors and developers. However, due to the high cost of motherboards based on AM5 and DDR5 memory, and motherboards with socket AM5 at the start of sales, they are rather a product for the future, which will primarily interest computer enthusiasts.

Intel Core i3 Alder Lake i3-12100F BOX
description:
Affordable 12th Gen Intel Core i3 4-core processor from the Alder Lake family. It is manufactured on the basis of an optimized 10nm process technology and is designed for installation in Socket 1700 motherboards. It is a representative of the entry-level class, has a modest heat dissipation of 65W and is not among the overclocking chips for enthusiasts. Unlike the older Core i5/i7/i9 processors from the Alder Lake family, which are equipped with performant and energy-efficient cores, this model uses exclusively performant Performance class cores.

They support Hyper-Threading automatic overclocking technology and are able to process two computational threads simultaneously. There are four such cores in total, in normal mode they operate at a frequency of 3.3 GHz, and in case of a lack of computing power, they can be accelerated to 4.3 GHz. Unlike previous generations of Core i3 chips, Intel Core i3 Alder Lake supports both the usual DDR4 RAM (maximum frequency 3200 MHz) and the new DDR5 class memory (maximum frequency 4800 MHz) with a limit of 128 GB. Such a processor is best suited for multi-purpose home systems, not too demanding workstations and entry-level gaming computers designed for gaming in Full HD resolution.

name: AMD Ryzen 7 Raphael 7700X BOX
description:
Ryzen 7 pre-top model The Ryzen 7 CPU is built on the all-new AMD Zen 4 architecture. The CPU is built on the advanced 5nm process technology, equipped with a fifth-generation PIC-E memory bus, tuned to work with DDR5 progressive RAM and supports AMD EXPO memory auto-overclocking technology . To install the processor, you will need a modern PC with a motherboard based on the new socket AM5, which was introduced in 2022.

The processor is equipped with 8 cores with a base clock speed of 4.5, which, when using Turbo Core technology, can automatically accelerate to 5.4 GHz. Thanks to the multithreading technology, each core can simultaneously execute two computational threads, which significantly increases the processor's performance under complex workloads. The amount of cache memory in comparison with Ryzen 7 of previous generations has doubled and is 32 MB.

The Ryzen 5 Raphael 7700X BOX saw a 29% increase in single-core performance over its predecessor by boosting clock speeds, increasing cache size, and optimizing the architecture. In general, the performance of the chip is approximately equal to the power of the previous generation Ryzen 9 CPU. Due to the initial high cost of DDR5 memory and motherboards with an AM5 socket, this model is an interesting processor option for growth, which will be of interest primarily to computer enthusiasts.

Intel Core i7 Raptor Lake i7-13700K BOX
description:
A near-top 16-core processor, shown in the fall of 2022 as part of the presentation of the 13th generation of Intel processors, codenamed Raptor Lake. Manufactured on an optimized 10nm process and designed for installation in LGA 1700 motherboards. It belongs to the upper price segment, designed for demanding gamers, streamers, coders, VFX specialists and other categories of consumers who need really powerful, but not too expensive processor.

A feature of the model is the use of a hybrid architecture, in which the cores are divided into 2 groups: high-performance Raptor Cove and auxiliary energy-efficient Gracemont. The former is involved in serious computing tasks, the latter work on the hook when solving simple background tasks. Core i7-13700K consists of these 16 cores (8P + 8E) clocked at 2.5GHz to 3.4GHz and auto-overclocked to 5.4GHz (TurboBoost Max 3.0 technology).

Hyper-Threading technology is supported only by P-cores. The unique feature of the chip lies in its ability to work with both DDR4 and more modern DDR5 RAM. The maximum clock frequency for DDR4 is 3200 MHz, for DDR5 - 5600 MHz. The maximum amount of RAM can be 128 GB. The processor is designed to be installed in a motherboard with a Socket 1700 socket, which is also compatible with 12th generation Intel processors. In the maximum load mode, the declared power dissipation is an impressive 253 W, so a powerful power supply and a high-quality cooling system are required in pair with the chip.

AMD Ryzen 5 Renoir-X 4500 BOX
description:
A representative of an unusual budget series of Renoir-X processors, which in all technical parameters is a representative of the middle class. The Ryzen 5 4500 processor is designed to work in tandem with motherboards based on AM4 system logic and DDR4 RAM. It supports dual-channel operation with a maximum RAM clock speed of 3200 MHz. To connect to a monitor, the system needs a full-fledged video card, since the processor does not have an integrated video core.

Priced at just under $100, it's built in the 6-core + 6-thread configuration that AMD typically uses in higher-end Ryzen 5/7 processors. The secret lies in the fact that due to the lack of suitable crystals, AMD engineers took Ryzen 4000U APU mobile processors as a basis. As a result, both are based on the same Zen 2 generation crystal and have similar characteristics. The difference lies in the fact that the desktop processor's clock speeds were raised (3.6 GHz in normal mode, 4.1 GHz in automatic overclocking mode), power consumption was increased to 65 W, and strict restrictions on exceeding it were removed.

name: Intel Core i9 Raptor Lake i9-13900KS BOX
Intel Core i7 Alder Lake i7-12700K BOX
description:
A high-performance 12-core processor from Intel, which was introduced to the public in 2021 as part of the 12th generation of chips, codenamed Alder Lake. It is based on a monolithic crystal produced using a 10-nm process technology and differs from its predecessors in the blue camp due to the use of hybrid cores. As in mobile ARM chips, it uses two types of computing cores: 8 productive Golden Cove cores and 4 energy-efficient Gracemont cores, the interaction of which is responsible for the new Thread Director technology.

Performance cores operate at clock speeds from 3.6 to 4.9 GHz, support Hyper-Threading technology and are used in resource-intensive tasks like processing game worlds, rendering, compiling, etc. In turn, energy-efficient E-cores are turned on when solving simple background tasks, in idle they operate at a frequency of 2.7 GHz, and if necessary, they can automatically overclock to 3.8 GHz.

In addition, the Core i7-12700K BOX, like all other members of the Alder Lake family, supports the simultaneous operation of DDR4 and DDR5 memory classes. To interact with the graphics card, a PCI-E 5.0 interface is provided. The processor is designed to install a PC with an LGA 1700 socket motherboard. The declared heat dissipation is 125 W in normal mode or 190 W at peak load. In the absence of a discrete graphics card, the monitor can be connected to the processor's built-in graphics card. Unlike previous generations of Intel Core, this is a more serious solution called UHD Graphics 770, which can comfortably play competitive games like FIFA 22, CS: GO and Dota 2.
